    "summary": "Currently I am a Physics Teacher, trying to instill the interest for the physics we can appreciate all around us, helping students graduate secondary school. I have taught/am teaching all senior secondary school levels in The Netherlands (i.e. 4&5 HAVO and 4&5&6 VWO, including final exam years) besides gaining more experience in teaching HAVO/VWO levels 2 and 3.\n\nBefore this job, I have always worked with management of information and knowledge in companies and organisations ranging from an international publisher, an aircraft manufacturer, a food ingredients producer, a semiconductors manufacturer and an international NGO. Worked on developing projects, writing project proposals and raising funds to realise them. As a second responsibility, I oversaw the regional (Latin American) program to promote healthy diets, food safety and food security.\n\nI like to facilitate people in finding the information they need for their daily activities, projects, studies, etc.\n\nSpecialties: setting up documentary information system; developing taxonomy; conversion to virtual library; international project management (e.g. improvement of information processes); able to communicate in Dutch, English and Spanish fluently, training/coaching; analysis of complex situations and environments.",
